    3. **Delete** a key (`delete <key>`)
    4. **List** all keys (`list`)
    
    ### Advanced Features (what makes it medium-hard)
    5. **Persistence**: Data survives program restarts (store in a JSON or custom binary format)
    6. **TTL (Time-To-Live)**: Keys can expire after N seconds (`set <key> <value> --ttl=60`)
    7. **Transactions**: Batch operations that either all succeed or all fail (`multi`, `exec`)
    8. **CLI Interface**: Accept commands from command line or interactive mode
    
    ### Example Usage
    ```bash
    # Interactive mode
    $ ./kvstore
    kv> set name "John Doe"
    OK
    kv> set session "abc123" --ttl=300
    OK
    kv> get name
    John Doe
    kv> list
    name, session
    ```
    
